# Title: Suspicious Kernel Dump Using Dtrace
# Author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)
# Date: 2021-12-28
# Level: high
# Description: Detects suspicious way to dump the kernel on Windows systems using dtrace.exe, which is available on Windows systems since Windows 10 19H1
# MITRE Tactic: Discovery
# Tags: attack.discovery, attack.t1082
# Reference: https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/windows/process_creation/proc_creation_win_dtrace_kernel_dump.yml

(CommandLine="*syscall:::return*" CommandLine="*lkd(*") OR (CommandLine="*lkd(0)*" Image="*\\dtrace.exe")